<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="icon" href="/images/pp.jpg" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Merienda:wght@300..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <title>The M's Hub - Fitness</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/style.css">
  <style>
    @media screen and (max-width: 500px) {
      .card {
        width: 100%;
      }
      header {
        padding: 10px;
      }
      .profile h1 {
        font-size: 1.5em;
      }
      .profile h2 {
        font-size: 1em;
      }
      .nav ul li {
        margin-right: 10px;
      }
    }

    .fitness {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      padding: 100px 0;
      text-align: center;
      color: #000;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .fitness::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      border-radius: 30px;
      background-color: aliceblue;
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      filter: blur(35px);
      opacity: 1.7;
      z-index: -1;
    }

    .fitness h2 {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: 28px;
    }

    .fitness h3 {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 24px;
    }

    .fitness ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .fitness li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .fitness button {
      margin-top: 20px;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 16px;
      background-color: #3498db;
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }

    .fitness button:hover {
      background-color: #2980b9;
    }

    .fitness video {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      max-width: 100%;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .fitness section {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    footer {
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #333;
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
    }

    video {
      width: 50%;
    }

    .slide {
      background-color: lightblue;
      border-radius: 50px;
    }

    .card {
      background-color: aliceblue;
      color: black;
    }

    img {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }

    /* Modal Styles */
    .modal {
      display: none;
      position: fixed;
      z-index: 9999;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100vw;
      height: 100vh;
      background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.95);
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .modal video {
      max-width: 100vw;
      max-height: 100vh;
      object-fit: contain;
      background-color: black;
    }

    .modal .close {
      position: absolute;
      top: 20px;
      right: 35px;
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 40px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      z-index: 10000;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

  <div class="fitness">
    <section id="sales"></section>

    <section class="slide" id="home-workouts">
      <h2>Home Workouts (Bodyweight)</h2>
      <p>Bodyweight workouts can be highly effective. They challenge your form, offering opportunities for improvement without needing gear or ample space.</p>

      <div id="prefers">
        <h3>I Prefer</h3>

        <h1>AIR SQUATS</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="squat" src="/videos/squat.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Lower your hips downward and backward, as if sitting in a chair.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Push through your feet to rise back to a standing position. Keep weight centered in your heels.</p>
        </div>

        <h1>PUSH-UPS</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="pushup" src="/videos/pushups.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Assume a plank position with shoulders above wrists. Engage core.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Lower body by bending elbows at a 45-degree angle.</p>
        </div>

        <h1>BURPEES</h1>
        <video autoplay loop playsinline muted aria-label="burpee" src="/videos/burpee.mp4"></video>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Steps</h2>
          <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Squat down, place hands on the ground, and jump feet back to a push-up position.</p>
          <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Push up, jump forward, then jump and clap overhead.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="advantages">
        <h3>Advantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Convenience and accessibility</li>
          <li>No need for expensive equipment</li>
          <li>Can be done anytime, anywhere</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div id="disadvantages">
        <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Limited variety of exercises</li>
          <li>Potential lack of motivation without a gym environment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="weight-training">
      <h2>Weight Training (Gym)</h2>
      <p>Find a trainer who specializes in weight training. They can create personalized workout plans, teach proper techniques, and help track progress.</p>
      <div id="advantages">
        <h3>Advantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Allows for progressive overload</li>
          <li>Can target specific muscle groups effectively</li>
          <li>Access to a wide range of equipment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div id="disadvantages">
        <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Requires a gym membership or equipment</li>
          <li>Potential risk of injury without proper form</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- Video Modal -->
  <div id="videoModal" class="modal">
    <span class="close">&times;</span>
    <video id="modalVideo" controls autoplay></video>
  </div>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>

  <script>
    // Open video in modal
    document.querySelectorAll('.fitness video').forEach(video => {
      video.addEventListener('click', function () {
        const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
        const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

        modal.style.display = "flex";
        modalVideo.src = this.src;
        modalVideo.play();
      });
    });

    // Close modal with X
    document.querySelector('.modal .close').addEventListener('click', () => {
      const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
      const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

      modal.style.display = "none";
      modalVideo.pause();
      modalVideo.src = "";
    });

    // Close modal by clicking outside video
    window.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
      const modal = document.getElementById("videoModal");
      const modalVideo = document.getElementById("modalVideo");

      if (event.target === modal) {
        modal.style.display = "none";
        modalVideo.pause();
        modalVideo.src = "";
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
